2.00	The_Royal_Canadian_Hussars_(Montreal)	The Royal Canadian Hussars (Montreal)	The Royal Canadian Hussars (Montreal) (abbreviated as RCH) is an armoured reconnaissance regiment of the Primary Reserve in the Canadian Forces. Its primary role consists in obtaining critical information about the belligerent as well as their surrounding terrain. It falls under the command of the 34th Canadian Brigade Group (34 CBG).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/5/54/Cap_badge_of_the_Royal_Canadian_Hussars.jpg/200px-Cap_badge_of_the_Royal_Canadian_Hussars.jpg
